name: Popeye the Sailor
overview:
Follows the adventures of the famed spinach-eating sailor man.

Popeye is one of the most popular cartoon characters of all time. This spunky but loveable spinach-eating sailor continues to delight young and old with his comic adventures, and the entire gang is around to provide plenty of rousing fun and action: Olive Oyl, Swee'Pea, Wimpy and Bluto.

episodes.name: Barbecue for Two
episodes.overview: Popeye wants to have a backyard barbecue with Olive Oyl, but is continually interrupted by a scheming Brutus, a hungry Wimpy and a crying Sweet Pea.

episodes.name: Hits And Missiles
episodes.overview: Popeye, Olive and Wimpy end up on the moon with little cheese men. They meet some moon men who introduce the trio to their leader, "Big Cheese." Popeye asks for help in getting back to Earth, but the leader is an evil man and tries to imprison Popeye and his friends. However, the moon men have taken a liking to Popeye and don't like the way that their leader has treated him, so they help him escape by overthrowing "Big Cheese."

episodes.name: Muskels Schmuskels
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive watch Brutus the strongman performing at the carnival. The two men quickly become rivals for Olive. But she makes Popeye promise not to fight.

episodes.name: Hoppy Jalopy
episodes.overview: Popeye in his junk-pile jalopy competes with Brutus in his slick race car to win a cross-country race. Brutus employs a series of dirty tricks to keep ahead, while keeping Olive Oyl trapped in his trunk.

episodes.name: Dead-Eye Popeye
episodes.overview: Sheriff Popeye captures villain Brutus McBride and throws the scum into jail. His gang of thugs start a big shoot-out in an attempt to free their leader.

episodes.name: Muellers Mad Monster
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive take shelter from a thunderstorm in Mad Mueller's castle. But Mueller's monster, Irving, takes a shine to Olive.

episodes.name: Caveman Capers
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Olive the story of how his ancestor Prehesterical Popeye discovered the magical powers of spinach and stopped Prehesterical Brutus.

episodes.name: Bullfighter Bully
episodes.overview: Popeye objects to how a bull is being treated by the matador in the bullring, then when Olive Is caught in the Bull, between the matador and the bull, he must use spinach to save the day.

episodes.name: Ace of Space
episodes.overview: Flying saucers have landed, Olive is unfortunate enough to be captured by a robot man looking for humans. Popeye must take control of the spaceship save Olive and get her home.

episodes.name: College Of Hard Knocks
episodes.overview: Olive the college student is infatuated with Professor Brutus and contemptuous of Popeye's lack of education, leading Popeye to enroll in college himself.

episodes.name: Abdominal Snowman
episodes.overview: Popeye hears talk of abominable snowman sightings and so decides to take it upon himself to investigate.

episodes.name: Ski-Jump Chump
episodes.overview: It's an ice cold winter, Popeye upsets a large hibernating bear while trying to impress Olive with his moves on the ski-jumps.

episodes.name: Irate Pirate
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive are out testing Popeyes new boat on a relaxing boat ride. When out in the ocean they meet Jolly Roger the pirate. Unfortunately Roger takes a fancy to Olive. The pirate kidnaps her and sets school of sharks after Popeye.

episodes.name: Foola-Foola Bird
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive are searching the jungle for the rare Foola-Foola bird. Following close behind is Brutus, also hunting the bird as there is a reward of a million dollar for finding it.

episodes.name: Uranium on the Cranium
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive set-sail to a desert island with a map citing the location of Uranium, unknown to them Brutus is already there, He plans on dressing like a gorilla and scaring them away.

episodes.name: Two-Faced Paleface
episodes.overview: Brutus dresses as a native Indian and claims the land as an Indian Reservation after Popeye strikes it lucky searching for gold in the old west. Popeye tries to beat him at his own game by dressing as an Indian too, declaring all out war.

episodes.name: Childhood Daze
episodes.overview: Brutus forces Popeye into the professor's aging machine, turning him into a 2 year old.

episodes.name: Sheepish Sheep-Herder
episodes.overview: Popeye volunteers to stand guard to protect Poopdeck Pappy's ranch, a rustler tries to get rid of Popeye but is driven mad by his ability to reappear right after he's been lassoed, tied up and even thrown off a cliff.

episodes.name: Track Meet Cheat
episodes.overview: Olive sees Brutus showing his athletic prowess at a track meet, Popeye gets jealous, runs on to the field and starts competing himself.

episodes.name: Crystal Ball Brawl
episodes.overview: Wimpy has acquired the SeaHags crystal ball, he is using it to bet on sporting events. Brutus realizes this and steal the crystal ball. Popeye gets suspicious, so sets a trap to get the ball back.

episodes.name: Interrupted Lullaby
episodes.overview: Brutus sinks to a new low in both greed and criminal activity by trying to abduct little Swee'pee from his family.

episodes.name: Sea No Evil
episodes.overview: As Popeye and Olive relax on their new boat "The Miss Olive" someone swims beneath stealing items from right under their nose. Luckily Brutus's boating store has a seemingly endless supply of stolen item replacements.

episodes.name: From Way Out
episodes.overview: A giant space magnet connected to the top of an astronomer's observatory pulls stuff from outer space to earth. One day it also pulls leather jacket wearing space greasers from Mars.

episodes.name: Seeing Double
episodes.overview: Popeye is jailed for committing a bank robbery which he insists he didn't commit. He must prove he didn't do it. In a seemingly unrelated subplot, two thugs build a Popeye robot to do their bidding.

episodes.name: Swee'pea Soup
episodes.overview: The citizens are revolting, they want a new king, someone sweet like Swee'pea! Professor Wotasnozzle suggests making a soup out of Swee'pea is the best way to become just like him.

episodes.name: Hag Way Robbery
episodes.overview: Popeye, Olive, Wimpy, and Swee' Pea, set-sail to The Sea Hag's island, She has kidnapped Eugene, the Jeep. Unknown to them The Sea Hag is following in her submarine waiting for an opportunity to remove all spinach from Popeye's boat.

episodes.name: The Lost City of Bubble-Lon
episodes.overview: The Professor, Popeye and their assistant Brutus are searching for the lost city of "Bubble-On". Popeye is suspicious, he thinks Brutus is more interested in taking the cities treasure than documenting scientific discoveries.

episodes.name: There's No Space Like Home
episodes.overview: Brutus beats up an alien he sees walking down the street, thinking its Popeye on the way to Olive Oyl's fancy dress party. The alien retaliates by trying to blow up the earth, Popeye and Brutus team up to stop him.

episodes.name: Potent Lotion
episodes.overview: Someone has sent Popeye a present, he opens it to find shaving lotion, thinking it's something Olive Oyl has bought for him he puts it on. From that moment everyone hates him.

episodes.name: Astro-Nut
episodes.overview: Popeye is undergoing a series of government tests, one of which involves using spinach to travel in a rocket at the speed of light. Meanwhile at home Brutus moves in on Olive.

episodes.name: Where There's a Will
episodes.overview: Popeye is called by a lawyer who tells him that he and Brutus are the beneficiaries of someone they know. And that he'll be reading the will at noon. And if one of them is not there at noon they will forfeit the inheritance. So Brutus tries to keep Popeye from getting there at noon.

episodes.name: Take It Easel
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus are rival artists, each of whom wants to win a magazine contest for the best original flower painting.

episodes.name: I Bin Sculped
episodes.overview: Olive is a sculptor and puts an ad in a shop window asking for a model. Popeye and Brutus both offer their services. Olive tells them she's not looking for someone who is strong and healthy but someone who is worn and tired. So both Popeye and Brutus try to mess themselves up but one of them always stops the other.

episodes.name: Fleas a Crowd
episodes.overview: Popeye is showing off his stage act, a flea circus, Brutus is tired of hearing the rave reviews about it so destroys the act by setting a dog loose on stage.

episodes.name: Popeye's Junior Headache
episodes.overview: Olive insists that Popeye babysit her Niece while she goes out, Popeye hasn't slept for 6 days and begins to fall asleep on the job, he gets put in a dress and Olive takes offence thinking he's making fun of her.

episodes.name: Egypt Us
episodes.overview: Popeye, Olive and Wimpy accidentally walk to Egypt, Olive is Kidnapped by Egyptians and taken to the temple below a Sphinx, Popeye goes to rescue her and Wimpy does what he does best, cook the hamburgers.

episodes.name: The Big Sneeze
episodes.overview: Popeye, Olive and Swee'Pea are on a skiing trip in the French Alps. But the vacation goes sour when someone steals Olive's raccoon coat.

episodes.name: The Last Resort
episodes.overview: Popeye, Olive and Wimpy Dimpy Doo find themselves in a spooky mansion Inn, full of apparent ghostly goings on. It turns out The Sea Hag is using the Inn as a hideout for printing counterfeit money. Jinkies!

episodes.name: Jeopardy Sheriff
episodes.overview: Poopdeck Pappy entertains Swee' Pea by telling him about his adventures in the old west. Popeye thinks he's lying and Pappy tries to prove it's true, which leads to Popeye rescuing him a lot.

episodes.name: Baby Phase
episodes.overview: Popeye drifts off to sleep while reading a book about juggling. He dreams Swee'Pea is the star juggler in a circus and is under the contract of a Brutus like ringmaster.

episodes.name: Goon with the Wind
episodes.overview: Olive is captured and taken to Goonland to marry the Goonking, Popeye is caged and his can of spinach is taken from him. The situation is looking grim all round.

episodes.name: Insultin' the Sultan
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive break up after a bitter argument. In a rage, Popeye joins the Foreign Legion. Meanwhile, a sultan decides Olive will be his 75th wife.

episodes.name: Dog-Gone Dog-Catcher
episodes.overview: Olives new dog is taken by Brutus the dog catcher, Popeye dresses up in a dog costume to save her. A chase takes place, Popeye escapes still dressed up as a dog, confusing Brutus, who thinks he's seen a talking dog.

episodes.name: Voice from the Deep or See Here, Sea Hag
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag has an entire island believing that she is the god from the deep, her plan is to get rid of the natives and open an expensive villains resort. Chief Knucklebone, who is not convinced, summons Popeye to investigate.

episodes.name: Matinee Idol Popeye
episodes.overview: Brutus is an egotistical French director making a film about Antony and Cleopatra, starring Popeye and Olive Oyl. But Popeye may not survive the production.

episodes.name: Beaver or Not
episodes.overview: Popeye visits the local stream for a relaxing swim but is surprised to find a couple of dam-building beavers. A battle begins and eventually Popeye admits defeat and goes for a swim in the beaver's reservoir.

episodes.name: Battery Up
episodes.overview: It's a big Baseball game between Popeye's team and Brutus's team, with Wimpy as the umpire what could possibly go wrong. Olive is rooting for Popeye, at least she is at first.

episodes.name: Deserted Desert
episodes.overview: Popeye Journeys to the Lost deserted desert in a quest to find The Lost Dutchman's Mine and its rumored contents, golden nuggets. Brutus is of course also in the desert waiting to steal the goldmines treasure.

episodes.name: Skinned Divers
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus are diving for buried treasure, Brutus however has more than sunken treasure in his eyes, he spies the lovely mermaid Olive Oyl.

episodes.name: Popeye's Service Station
episodes.overview: Popeye is now the manager of a service station, he provides a good service with free extras. Brutus comes along only wanting the free extras, including free access to another customer, Olive Oyl.

episodes.name: Coffee House
episodes.overview: That bad daddy-o Brutus gets the upper hand on Popeye in their rivalry for Olive by catering to her sudden decision to become a beatnik. Can the groovy cool cat defeat the hot dog?

episodes.name: Popeye's Pep-Up Emporium
episodes.overview: Come to Popeye's gym, everyone from Brutus to Wimpy welcome. As the commercial says, he Builds the flat and reduces the fat.

episodes.name: Bird Watcher Popeye
episodes.overview: To stop Brutus and Popeye fighting over her, Olive Oyl suggests that they take up a hobby, like bird watching. Popeye likes this idea but Brutus would rather watch other things.

episodes.name: Time Marches Backwards
episodes.overview: Popeye goes back to the caveman days in The Professor's time machine. When he gets there he finds Caveman Wimpy trying to catch a cow and Olive in need of saving from Caveman Brutus.

episodes.name: Hillbilly Dilly
episodes.overview: Olive and Popeye drive for an outing in the mountains and meet up with the McGoofs and the Hitchfields feuding and get themselves involved. Popeye eventually bests both clans and stops the feud.

episodes.name: Popeye's Pet Store
episodes.overview: Popeye the pet store owner likes to keep his customers satisfied. Olive, Wimpy and Swee'Pea come buy pets and leave satisfied. Someone then kidnaps all their pets. Popeye dons a dog disguise and tries to find the culprit...... in a 'suprise' twist, It's Brutus.

episodes.name: Ballet de Spinach
episodes.overview: Brutus make fun of Popeye for donning a ballet costume and taking to the stage with Olive.

episodes.name: Sea Hagracy
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag tries to tempt Popeye and Wimpy into a life of piracy.

episodes.name: Spinach Shortage
episodes.overview: Brutus is a business tycoon who corners the market on spinach, causing a shortage that makes it impossible for Popeye to find any.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Dragon
episodes.overview: Popeye buys a suit of armor, hires a horse and goes off to save Princess Olive from a dragon.

episodes.name: Popeye the Fireman
episodes.overview: Wimpy see Olive calling for help from a smoke filled hotel room, fireman Popeye is called out to save her, it turns out to be smoke from Mr Brutus's cigar.

episodes.name: Popeye's Pizza Palace
episodes.overview: Things aren't going to plan at Popeye's pizza Palace, Wimpy as usual is trying to get a free lunch while Brutus constantly asks for pizza topping which are not on the menu.

episodes.name: Down the Hatch
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Swee'pea all about the olden days when his ancestor, captain Popeye ruled the seas. The adventure he recites involves Captain Popeye saving Wimpy's ship from the evil Pirate Brutus.

episodes.name: Lighthouse Keeping
episodes.overview: Olive Oyl visits Popeye at his lighthouse. Brutus is an unwelcome tag-along who proves worse than worthless when a shark causes trouble.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Phantom
episodes.overview: Popeye is haunted and taunted by a mischievous ghost who steals his spinach.

episodes.name: Popeye's Picnic
episodes.overview: While out on a picnic Olive and comes face to face with a giant bull while Popeye's car gets a flat tire.

episodes.name: Out of This World
episodes.overview: Popeye uses The Professors time machine to take Olive, Swee' Pea and himself on a trip to the moon. When there they find it's just like earth. .. No reason is given to how or way it's no longer populated by little cheese people, presumably the moon men killed them all and stole their land.

episodes.name: Madame Salami
episodes.overview: Big hairy Madam Salami tells Olive that in order for Popeye to prove his love he must be able to perform several impossible acts. The bearded Madame Salami is then astounded when Popeye manages to perform the feats.

episodes.name: Timber Toppers
episodes.overview: Popeye's a lumberjack and he's alright, he works all day and sleeps all night. Brutus is also a lumberjack, he steals Popeye's trees and his best gal', Popeye ends up tied to a tree heading for the chopper.

episodes.name: Skyscraper Capers
episodes.overview:
Brutus hires Popeye to Build on his site  It comes to beatings as both of them fight.

Throughout the punches Wimpy eat's a dinner and Popeye the sailor comes out as the winner.

episodes.name: Private-Eye Popeye
episodes.overview: Popeye, Olive and The Jeep are hired to search for someone smuggling diamonds by boat. Discriminating based on previous offenses Popeye suspects Brutus and his pickle importing scheme are a cover.

episodes.name: Little Olive Riding Hood
episodes.overview: Little Olive Riding Hood is delivering hamburgers to her sick friend, Mr. Wimpy. The Sea Hag wants those hamburgers for herself.

episodes.name: Popeye's Hypnotic Glance
episodes.overview: Brutus hypnotizes Olive into falling in love with him. Then he hypnotizes Alice the Goon into falling in love with Popeye.

episodes.name: Popeye's Trojan Horse
episodes.overview: A sawfish, a Trojan horse, two princes and a damsel in distress figure in Popeye's storybook tale to a skeptical Swee'Pea.

episodes.name: Frozen Feuds
episodes.overview: Alice the Goon is terrorizing a small town. Popeye decides he wants to try and catch this monster, legend has it that just looking at Alice will make you so scared that you will turn white and stay that way forever.

episodes.name: Popeye's Corn-Certo
episodes.overview: A classic cartoon duel in music, Olive, The master of ceremonies presents Popeye - the modern music master and the Bach of the Backwoods - Brutus.

episodes.name: Westward Ho-Ho
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Swee'pea the tale of Grandpappy Popeye who accidentally joined the prairie schooner, a wagon train, thinking it was a ship.

episodes.name: Popeye's Cool Pool
episodes.overview: When the heat is so unbearable and being nagged by Olive and Swee Pea, Popeye decides to build his own swimming pool. His neighbour Brutus wants to use it but Popeye won't let him.

episodes.name: Jeep Jeep
episodes.overview: Swee'pea makes a new friend, Eugene the magic future predicting Jeep, Brutus realizes that the Jeep can answer questions about the future and plots with The Sea Hag to Jeepnapp him.

episodes.name: Popeye's Museum Piece
episodes.overview: Popeye is the custodian of a museum. He gets involved with an art thief named Brutus.

episodes.name: Golf Brawl
episodes.overview: Popeye, Wimpy, Olive and Brutus compete against each other in a golf tournament.

episodes.name: Wimpy's Lunch Wagon
episodes.overview: Wimpy leaves Popeye in charge of his hamburger wagon while he goes to the bank. The villains wreck the place.

episodes.name: Weather Watchers
episodes.overview: Brutus is after Popeye's job as a weather forecaster.Through sly tricks, Brutus gets Popeye's weather predictions fouled up.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Magic Hat
episodes.overview: Brutus, the magician, involves Popeye in his act. He makes him appear ridiculous to the audience. Popeye gets mad, fights Olive, stops the fight and gets involved in a magic act too. Jeep is part of Brutus' act. A magic wand turns characters into various animals until Popeye manages to get the wand. This leads to a big fight in a magic hat between Brutus and Popeye.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Giant
episodes.overview: Wimpy eats "grow pills" and becomes a Paul Bunyon-like freak in a carnival. Brutus, the carnival owner, cannot make money on Wimpy -- he eats too many hamburgers. Brutus finally leaves Wimpy in Popeye's care. Popeye, with the help of Swee' Pea and Swee' Pea's chemistry set, invent a reducing pill to bring Wimpy back to normal.

episodes.name: Pests of the Pecos
episodes.overview: Brutus, "the most feared desperado of the early west," robs a train and comes to a town called GRAVESTONE FLATS, where he tangles with Popeye, the Sheriff.

episodes.name: The Blubbering Whaler
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Swee' Pea the story of how he once sung baby whales to sleep. The bedtime story is about the ship, Morpheus, its skipper, Captain Brutus, and Popeye, the harpoonist. Popeye refuses to harpoon a big mama who shipwrecks the Morpheus. Swee' Pea wants to know how Popeye got off the island.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Spinach Stalk
episodes.overview: Popeye climbs a giant spinach stalk and finds that Brutus the giant has kidnapped Olive and Eugene the Jeep in this skewed retelling of "Jack and the Beanstalk."

episodes.name: Shoot the Chutes
episodes.overview: Olive wants Popeye to win the championship parachute jump. Brutus also enters, Popeye starts to fall fast, but lands on top of Brutus' parachute.

episodes.name: Tiger Burger
episodes.overview: Popeye and Wimpy are in deepest darkest India, the natives are terrified of a man-eating tiger named Conga. Popeye wants to capture but Conga grabs Wimpy first.

episodes.name: Bottom Gun
episodes.overview: Brutus the cattle rustler goes to Wimpy's food wagon for breakfast, he wants ham and eggs but find Wimpy only has hamburgers. Brutus decides to swipe eggs from Popeye's all american chicken ranch.

episodes.name: Olive Drab and the Seven Sweapeas
episodes.overview: Once upon a time, there lived a beautiful Princess named Olive Drab. A shipment of gold meant for the castle is stolen by the Sea Hag. Olive's father sends her after Prince Popeye to retrieve the gold. Olive enlists the aid of the seven Swee' Peas. Together, they find Prince Popeye and he battles Sea Hag to get back the gold.

episodes.name: Blinkin Beacon
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag has kidnapped Swee' Pea and sent her vultures after Popeye.

episodes.name: Azteck Wreck
episodes.overview: Olive, Popeye and Jeep are at the Aztec ruins in Mexico. They discover that the Jeep can read the carvings, which starts them on a quest for Aztec treasure. Brutus, their Mexican guide, appropriates the Jeep to find the treasure.

episodes.name: The Green Dancin' Shoes
episodes.overview: Olive is a poor girl who lives in the wood, her sailor sweetheart, Popeye, is also poor and can not afford to take her dancing. While walking in the woods Olive meets the Sea Hag who trades a pair of her dancing shoes for a sea shell. The shoes are cursed and force Olive to dance forever without stopping.

episodes.name: Spare Dat Tree
episodes.overview: Popeye tries to protect an historical tree, Brutus, the woodsman, tries to cut it down.

episodes.name: The Glad Gladiator
episodes.overview: Popeye is transported by the time machine to the center of the Coliseum in Rome, Brutus Nero, is annoyed by his girlfriend's interest in Popeye. He makes Popeye battle gladiators, lions and himself.

episodes.name: The Golden Touch
episodes.overview: Popeye is king who is noted for making his people happy by giving them everything. He is therefore very poor. Popeye receives the golden touch by wishing on a star and summoning a jeep, who warns him beforehand that it will not make him happy. Popeye wants to be rid of the golden touch. The jeep makes him stop the Sea Hag from chasing Jeeps first. He does it with the help of spinach and lives happily ever after.

episodes.name: Hamburger Fishing
episodes.overview: Wimpy catches a cow, who is really an enchanted princess. She grants him three wishes for letting her go, but the Sea Hag demands he use the wishes to make gold.

episodes.name: Popeye the Popular Mechanic
episodes.overview: Popeye buys a do-it-yourself kit and makes a mechanical servant. It continues its mechanical duties all through the night, pouring tea on Popeye, mixing salad in his mouth and tossing other items. It lights a match, causing Popeye to awaken blowing flames. Popeye ends by putting the mechanical servant in workshop vice. Popeye then does his own house work in an uncomplaining manner.

episodes.name: Popeye's Folly
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Swee' Pea the story of building the first steamboat, "Popeye's Folly", Brutus, the captain of the windjammer challenges "Folly" to a race.

episodes.name: Popeye's Used Car
episodes.overview: Popeye arrives at Olive's house to take her for a walk. She refuses and rides off with Brutus in his new car. Popeye goes to Wimpy's used car lot, and Wimpy sells him a car.

episodes.name: Spinachonara
episodes.overview: Popeye reads Swee' Pea a Japanese fairytale. Popeye, Wimpy, Olive and Brutus are all used as characters.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Polite Dragon
episodes.overview: A dragon steps out of swee'peas storybook, he tries to be kind and helpful, but sneezes fire and the whole house goes up in flames. It ends with Popeye holding Swee' Pea in his lap in charred remains, reading fairytale book.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Ugly Ducklin
episodes.overview: Popeye shows Swee' Pea a picture of himself, Olive and Brutus when they were children, he says that he was called the Ugly Ducklin'. One day after being bullied by Brutus for being very, very ugly, popeye set sail to a small island inhabited by goons, they were friendly and fed him sea spinach. The spinach made him powerful and very close to being handsome.

episodes.name: Popeye's Tea Party
episodes.overview: Popeye is sent back in time to The Boston Tea Party. The local residents are fed up with being overtaxed, so they plot to throw the tea overboard into the sea.

episodes.name: The Troll Wot Got Gruff
episodes.overview: Once again Popeye tells Swee'pea a fairy story using his friends and family as characters. Brutus is the troll.

episodes.name: Popeye the Lifeguard
episodes.overview: Popeye's a lifeguard and all the girls on the beach are falling for him. Olive is jealous and tries to get his attention by diving off a pier and yelling help! Popeye rescues her and is very angry because she took him away from all the girls.

episodes.name: Popeye in the Woods
episodes.overview: Popeye and Wimpy camp to the woods for peace and quiet but Wimpy wants to cook hamburgers.

episodes.name: After the Ball Went Over
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus play ping pong, and the prize is a kiss from Olive.

episodes.name: Popeye and Buddy Brutus
episodes.overview: Brutus asks Popeye to be his skin diving buddy. Popeye agrees. Popeye finds an ancient western sea cow town. Popeye finds gold, Brutus takes half, then hits Popeye and takes Popeye's share. Wimpy is fishing and catches Brutus on his line. The episode ends with Wimpy having his picture taken with Brutus hanging beside him like a big whale.

episodes.name: Popeye's Car Wash
episodes.overview: Popeye opens a car wash. Brutus has a car wash across the street. When Olive brings a long convertible to Popeye to be washed, Brutus mixes the controls and Olive's car comes out shrunken to midget size. Olive is burned up and Brutus takes her across the street to his beautiful "Brutus Beauty Bath." Olive swoons over Brutus and he chases her. Popeye comes to the rescue and gets the worst of it. Then he eats spinach. Popeye knocks Brutus' car wash apart and it settles back to Brutus' junk yard. Brutus lands in front of Popeye's Car Wash in the form of a statue spraying water from his mouth and ears. Popeye and Olive hop in the car and drive into his car wash singing.

episodes.name: Camel Aires
episodes.overview: Popeye travels to Egypt in the hopes of recovering a rare gem and bringing it to the USA.

episodes.name: Plumbers Pipe Dream
episodes.overview: Popeye's attempts to fix Olive's leaking pipework leads to an escalating series of disasters that culminate in flooding all of New York City.

episodes.name: Popeye and the Herring Snatcher
episodes.overview: Wimpy, a night watchman in a herring factory, gets a cold and asks Popeye to take over. He hears strange noises and starts investigating, many hijinx follow and Brutus turns up.

episodes.name: Invisible Popeye
episodes.overview: Olive accidentally switches on the Professor's time machine, which takes her to a bizarre Mars-like planet. Popeye takes invisibility pills and goes to rescue her.

episodes.name: The Square Egg
episodes.overview: Swee' Pea has a square egg, did he find it or did he lay it? However he got it (Porabably from Popeye's chicken ranch) it's very rare and valuable.

episodes.name: Old Salt Tale
episodes.overview: while at the beach Popeye tells Swee'Pea a tall tale that explains why the sea is salty.

episodes.name: Jeep Tale
episodes.overview: Popeye is telling Swee'Pea a fairytale about a mama jeep and her four children -- three good girls and a mischievous boy named Jeepers. One day they go to eat spinach in the good farmer's garden. Jeepers goes into the bad farmer's garden and eats weeds. The farmer catches Jeepers and locks him up, but mama rescues him that night. The next day, the bad farmer tries to chop down the jeep tree, but mama jeep foils him completely. Afterward, the good farmer invites them over for more spinach.

episodes.name: The Super Duper Market
episodes.overview: Olive, Popeye and Wimpy are shopping at a Supermarket where Brutus is manager.

episodes.name: Golden-Type Fleece
episodes.overview: Popeye goes back in time to ancient Greece. The king, mistaking him for Hercules sends him to capture the Golden Fleece. Zeus isn't happy about this and send out wave after wave of thunderbolt rain!!!

episodes.name: Popeye the White Collar Man
episodes.overview: Olive convinces Popeye to become a white collar worker. Popeye is hired as an insurance agent. His first assignment is to sell a policy to a stunt man. Popeye follows him on all his stunts, trying to get him to listen to his pitch. Popeye is getting the worst of it. The stunt man is so happy he did not have to take the falls himself, he signs the policy. The episode ends with Popeye bandaged from head to toe being wheeled into the insurance office by Olive to tell the boss he made the sale.

episodes.name: Sweapea Thru the Looking Glass
episodes.overview: Olive Oyl asks Popeye how the mirror was broken. He tells her that Swee' Pea was wondering what was inside the mirror so he walked through it and found himself in a meadow. Swee' Pea fell into a hole and found himself in a small house. He ate some pills and grew very tall. Then he ate a different pill and returned to normal size. Outside, he found a garden where Queen Sea Hag and King Brutus were playing croquet, using Jeeps for balls and vultures for mallets. He refused to play so the Queen ordered him killed. He escaped through the mirror. To prove that Swee' Pea could not possibly have gone through the mirror, Popeye crashes into it and it breaks.

episodes.name: The Black Knight
episodes.overview: Popeye is transported back in time (AGAIN!) to the days of King Arthur and the Knights of the Roundtable. While there he is challenged to joust by 'Black Knight Brutus'.

episodes.name: Jingle Jangle Jungle
episodes.overview: Popeye, Olive and Brutus go on a safari in Africa hunting the big game, while In the jungle, Popeye and Brutus compete to get Olive a tiger skin.

episodes.name: The Day Silky Went Blozo
episodes.overview: King Blozo is upset that the minster "Silky" (so called because of his silky smooth mode of speech) has all the subjects in his kingdom addled. Blozo calls upon his noble varlet, Popeye, to get rid of the beast. However, when he does, Silky sweet-talks the King into letting him be.

episodes.name: Rip Van Popeye
episodes.overview: Popeye is reading a bedtime story, Popeye imagines himself as Daniel Boone tied to the railroad tracks by Indians. He awakens when the train falls on him in an attempt to escape.

episodes.name: Mississippi Sissy
episodes.overview: On a Mississippi riverboat, the villainous Jean Baptiste le Brute chases Olive, demanding a mysterious letter. Olive gives it to Popeye so that the brutish le Brute can't get it.

episodes.name: Double Cross Country Feet Race
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus compete in a cross-country foot race to Los Angeles and back. The winner is to receive a date with the lovely Olive Oyl. However, during the race, Brutus resorts to cheating to try to win, but Popeye sees through his tricks and wins the race and the date with Olive.

episodes.name: Fashion Fotography
episodes.overview: Olive wants to have her picture taken for a fashion magazine, Popeye and Brutus fight over who will take the pictures.

episodes.name: I Yam Wot I Yamnesia
episodes.overview: Popeye, Swee' Pea, Olive Oyl and Wimpy all switch voices. Brutus then enters and the plot becomes even more entangled.

episodes.name: Paper Pasting Pandemonium
episodes.overview: Olive wants her house re-wallpapered, Popeye and Brutus get into a dreadful mess whiel doing the job.

episodes.name: Coach Popeye
episodes.overview: Popeye tries to teach Swee' Pea about the importance of good sportsmanship.

episodes.name: Popeyed Columbus
episodes.overview: Popeye is transported back in time to the days of Christopher Columbus.

episodes.name: Popeye Revere
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Swee' Pea about his Great-Great-Great-Grand Pappy Poop Deck Revere.

episodes.name: Popeye in Haweye
episodes.overview: Olive is a tourist in Hawaii and Popeye and Brutus are tour guides.

episodes.name: Forever Ambergris
episodes.overview: Popeye is babysitting Swee' Pea, he tells the story of where Olive's perfume comes from.

episodes.name: Popeye de Leon
episodes.overview: Popeye decides to give Swee' Pea a history lesson and tell him about his grandfather Popeye De Leon.

episodes.name: Popeyed Fisherman
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Swee' Pea about a hungry fisherman who catches a cow that looks live Olive.

episodes.name: Popeye in the Grand Steeple Chase
episodes.overview: Olive wants Popeye to enter a steeplechase so he purchases a horse from Brutus.

episodes.name: Uncivil War
episodes.overview: Popeye teaches Swee' Pea about the ethics of being a good driver.

episodes.name: Popeye the Piano Mover
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus are piano movers; Olive Oyl is the owner of a piano that needs moving; and Wimpy is a traffic cop who takes chase when Popeye and the runaway piano tear down the street.

episodes.name: Popeye's Testimonial Dinner
episodes.overview: Popeye is to be honoured at a dinner for his brave deeds, Brutus tries to besmirch Popeye's outstanding record.

episodes.name: Around the World in Eighty Ways
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus take part in a race around the world to win a barrel full of money. Numerous mishaps follow.

episodes.name: Popeye's Fixit Shop
episodes.overview: Brutus becomes jealous when Popeye's business appears to be doing very well. When Olive needs something fixed, Brutus tries to discredit Popeye's ability to fix things.

episodes.name: Bell Hop Popeye
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus work as bellhops and compete for Olive.

episodes.name: The Ghost Host
episodes.overview: While out driving, Popeye and Olive must take shelter from the rain in an old house on a hill. Unbeknownst to them, it is 'the Haunted House (Strangers Welcome)', and they are mercilessly harassed by three ghosts until Popeye eats his spinach and drives them out of the house.

episodes.name: Strikes, Spares, an' Spinach
episodes.overview: Popeye takes Olive Oyl out for some bowling lessons, only to find ol' Brutus up to his mischievous shenanigans. Brutus finds out that Popeye has a date to take Olive bowling. Brutus rushes over to Olive's house to tell her that Popeye has a date with a blonde, and that he asked him to keep the date with Olive. Popeye arrives in the nick of time, and Brutus laughs it off as a gag. While Popeye is teaching Olive how to bowl, Brutus messes things up- unbeknownst to them- until Popeye catches him in the act. Popeye eats his spinach, then chases and catches Brutus. Popeye shapes Brutus into a bowling ball, which Popeye throws, knocking over a row of ashcans.

episodes.name: Jeep Is Jeep
episodes.overview: Olive asks Popeye to mind Swee'Pea while she goes to the beauty parlor. Popeye has difficulty keeping Swee'Pea amused when a package arrives for him. Opening the mysterious box, Popeye finds Eugene the Jeep, which is a birthday present. While he puts the Jeep through some magical tricks that the note explains, Swee'Pea crawls out of the house. When Popeye discovers that Swee'Pea is missing, he employs the Jeep to find him. The jeep leads him on a wild goose chase, and he saves Swee'Pea from a precarious spot. Unbeknownst to him, the Jeep takes Swee'Pea home. Olive comes back, and finding Swee'Pea alone, she blames Popeye for it when he zips back to the house.

episodes.name: The Spinach Scholar
episodes.overview: Olive tells Popeye that she's through with him unless he goes back to school and gets an "edumacation." Popeye enrolls in school and he is placed in the eighth grade. Popeye's many educated guesses cause him to become the laughingstock of the entire school. Each time that he attempts to answer a question in class, he's demoted. Poor Popeye can't cut it and goes through each class (from high school to kindergarten). Here, he's asked to spell "CAT." In desperation, he eats his spinach and spells it right, thus graduating from kindergarten. When Olive meets him after school, he brags that getting an education was very easy- he went through the whole school in one day.

episodes.name: Psychiatricks
episodes.overview: Brutus convinces Olive that Popeye must be cured of fighting over the least provocation. and he recommends a psychiatrist. When Popeye comes to visit Olive, she drags him in a confused state to the doctor to help him cope with his fighting habits. The sailor takes the talking cure to determine the root of his aggressive behavior. The psychiatrist's diagnosis is that spinach is the cause of his "fighting neurosis." But doesn't Professor Ed Shrinker look a bit like Brutus? When Popeye reluctantly throws away his can of spinach, the professor reveals himself to be Brutus, and he proceeds to beat the daylights out of Popeye. Olive feeds Popeye the spinach in the nick of time and turns the tables on Brutus. This cartoon includes flashbacks to Popeye's childhood, including a young Olive and a kid Brutus.

episodes.name: Rags to Riches to Rags
episodes.overview: Wimpy inherits a million dollars and lives it up in a grand style with an English butler. He decides to double his fortune by waging his fortune in a boxing match, betting on Kid Nitro to beat Popeye in a prize fight. To insure his investment, he manages to referee the bout. In the ring, Wimpy and his butler pull dirty tricks on Popeye to make sure that he doesn't win. When Popeye's finally knocked out, Wimpy doesn't have the heart to count his friend out in spite of his bet. Before the count of ten, he feeds Popeye his spinach, and Popeye quickly disposes of Kid Nitro and Wimpy's newly-found fortune.

episodes.name: Hair Cut-Ups
episodes.overview: Popeye takes Swee'Pea to the barber for a haircut but he's to scared and won't remove his hat. So Popeye tells him the story of Samson, the man who believed he got his strength from his long hair.

episodes.name: Poppa Popeye
episodes.overview: After losing Swee'Pea to a circus performer who passes himself off as the boy's long-lost father, Popeye goes through so much depression that he starts to act like a baby.

episodes.name: Quick Change Olie
episodes.overview: Popeye and Wimpy go back in time to the "ollie days", thanks to the Wiffle Bird.

episodes.name: The Valley of the Goons
episodes.overview: Popeye accidentally joins a tough bloodthirsty crew who are traveling to Goonland for a cargo of Goonskin.

episodes.name: Me Quest for Poopdeck Pappy
episodes.overview: Popeye discovers he's not an orphan after all. An old man who looks just like him lives on a faraway island, and now Popeye is on a quest to find him. Remake of the 1938 theatrical short "Goonland".

episodes.name: Mopey Hick
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag tricks Popeye into attacking a benevolent whale.

episodes.name: Mirror Magic
episodes.overview: A fairy-tale kingdom is ruled by the land's strongest man, ruthless King Brutus, but his magic mirror informs him of a potential challenger in Popeye.

episodes.name: It Only Hurts When They Laugh
episodes.overview: Olive forces Popeye and Brutus to laugh their way to friendship.

episodes.name: Wimpy the Moocher
episodes.overview: Rough House is prepared to resist any and all of Wimpy's attempts to cheat him out of hamburgers. Wimpy's con job begins with buying a single raw oyster.

episodes.name: Voo-Doo to You Too
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag makes Olive Oyl her zombie slave and puts a voodoo spell on Popeye that keeps his arms stuck to his sides. Only Eugene the Jeep can help him now.

episodes.name: Popeye Goes Sale-ing
episodes.overview: Olive drags Popeye into a nasty department store sale.

episodes.name: Popeye's Travels
episodes.overview: Popeye's journey in this episode is based upon the Lilliputian adventure from the classic novel Gulliver's Travels.

episodes.name: Incident at Missile City
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive are summoned to Spinachia by their old friend King Blozo who is in dire need of the sailor's might after his kingdom started being invaded by a daily barrage of non-explosive missiles.

episodes.name: Dog Catcher Popeye
episodes.overview: On the way back to his ship, Popeye befriends a little puppy that has a can tied to his tail. The abandoned puppy insists on following the sailor despite the latter's warnings that dogs are not allowed on his ship. After many attempts, Popeye evades the canine orphan and is on his way again, when dogcatcher Brutus nabs the pup. Each time Popeye gets the dog free, Brutus captures it again. Finally, with the aid of his spinach, Popeye rescues the dog. In the end, Popeye takes the puppy with him by tying a raft (with a doghouse on it) to the back of his ship.

episodes.name: What's News
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive travel to the small town Puddleburg where Popeye bought a newspaper company 'Puddleburg Splash'. Olive plans to teach the townspeople how to read but bullies tear down the new school. Popeye defeats the bullies and starts her classes.

episodes.name: Spinach Greetings
episodes.overview: The evil Sea Hag interrupts Popeye's family Christmas

episodes.name: The Baby Contest
episodes.overview: Wimpy is the judge in a baby contest, Popeye and Olive enter Swee'Pea while Brutus enters his own child.

episodes.name: Oil's Well That Ends Well
episodes.overview: Brutus swindles Olive Oyl out of her game show winnings with a worthless oil well. It's up to Popeye to grease the path towards a happy ending.

episodes.name: Amusement Park
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive stop by Brutus's Garage after running out of gas. But Brutus sabotages Popeye's car and steals away Olive.

episodes.name: Motor Knocks
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive stop by Brutus's Garage after running out of gas. But Brutus sabotages Popeye's car and steals away Olive.

episodes.name: Duel to the Finish
episodes.overview: Brutus kidnaps swee'pee and sells him to an amusement park freak-show.

episodes.name: Gem Jam
episodes.overview: In India, the Sea Hag hypnotizes Olive into stealing the sacred emerald from the crown of a jade idol, which puts a curse on the unwitting thief.

episodes.name: The Bathing Beasts
episodes.overview: Olive's new car attracts the attention of Popeye and Brutus, an argument breaks out over who will sit in the front seat, to settle things Olive suggests they enter a strong-man contest and the winner sits in the front.

episodes.name: The Rain Breaker
episodes.overview: Popeye meets Thor The God of Thunder and must save a fair maiden trapped high in ye olde castle.

episodes.name: Messin' Up the Mississippi
episodes.overview: Popeye becomes the headline attraction on a show-boat, Brutus as always, is jealous of his fame.

episodes.name: Love Birds
episodes.overview: Popeye buys Olive's lovebird a boyfriend. The two lovebirds, named Romeo and Juliet, quarrel and Romeo flies away. Olive demands that Popeye bring him back.

episodes.name: Sea Serpent
episodes.overview: Olive doesn't have time to be with Popeye. When she meets a man who knows about a Sea Serpent, Popeye is incredulous and finds evidence that he is a fake

episodes.name: Boardering on Trouble
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus are owners of a nightclub and restaurant, a fight breaks out between them when their guest, Miss Oyl, can't decide on spending her night at dinner or watching a show.

episodes.name: Aladdin's Lamp
episodes.overview: Popeye chases down the Sea Hag in order to take back the magic lamp she stole from Olive.

episodes.name: Butler Up
episodes.overview: An old school friend of Olive Oyl's turns up for dinner, to impress him Olive asks Popeye to be her butler.

episodes.name: The Leprechaun
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag steals a leprechaun's gold, the leprechaun turns to Popeye for help.

episodes.name: County Fair
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus are farmers who enter a county fair contest to see who's the best.

episodes.name: Hamburgers Aweigh
episodes.overview: Wimpy hears that Popeye has a cargo of Hamburgers, he offers to help protect them.

episodes.name: Popeye's Double Trouble
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag tries to curse Popeye with bad luck, But accidently gives him three wishes instead.

episodes.name: Kiddie Kapers
episodes.overview: Brutus goes to see the Sea Hag in the hopes that she will make him a youth potion to impress Olive. The potion changes his whole appearance and everything goes to plan until Olive finds out who he really is.

episodes.name: The Mark of Zero
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Olive's niece the story of the Mark of Zero, starring himself as the good guy and Brutus as the villain.

episodes.name: Myskery Melody
episodes.overview: Poopdeck Pappy is suddenly frightened of a mysterious flute melody that wafts through the air. At first Popeye and Olive cannot hear the haunting melody, but Pappy tells them about when he was attracted to a young woman, a jewel of the sea, who tried to seduce him but turned out to be Wicked Seahag in disguise.

episodes.name: Scairdy Cat
episodes.overview: Popeye drinks a potion which turns him into a coward, Brutus tries to take his place as Olive Oyl's date and Popeye finally manages to get hold of some spinach which gives him back his bravery.

episodes.name: Operation Ice-Tickle
episodes.overview: Olive tells Popeye and Brutus she'll go out with the first one who brings her back the North Pole -- which turns out to be an actual pole with red and white stripes.

episodes.name: The Cure
episodes.overview: Wimpy realizes he has a problem with hamburgers, Popeye helps him to contact Hamburger Anonymous. Meanwhile the SeaHag realizes her burger bar is missing it's best customer and takes steps to ruin Wimpy's attempts to break his addiction.

episodes.name: William Won't Tell
episodes.overview: It's 1813, King Brutus and Maiden Olive Oyl become jealous when Popeye rescues The Queen and fixes her broken carriage.

episodes.name: Pop Goes the Whistle
episodes.overview: Swee' Pea's favorite toy has lost its whistle and Popeye runs all over town trying to find it.

episodes.name: Autographically Yours
episodes.overview: Brutus is jealous of Popeyes fame.

episodes.name: A Poil for Olive Oyl
episodes.overview: It's Olive Oyl's birthday. When Popeye asks her what she would like as a present, she chooses a pearl necklace. However, Popeye decides that the stores charge too much for them, and he tries to make his own by diving into the deep blue sea for his own pearls... but the Sea Hag claims that the pearls belong to her!

episodes.name: My Fair Olive
episodes.overview: Popeye and Olive are on a date at the local museum and see knights on exhibit. The curator (Brutus) and Ms. Oyl fall for one another. When Brutus butts in and he and Popeye start to fight over Olive, she suggests that they have a jousting tournament to settle their argument.

episodes.name: Giddy Gold
episodes.overview: Popeye (The Sailor) and Olive (Oyl) discover an old sealed mine full of diamonds. Olive takes some of them and they must face many traps and dangers to exit the cave.

episodes.name: Strange Things Are Happening
episodes.overview: Popeye has a very strange day, The Sea Hag tries to kidnap him, Wimpy offers to buy him lunch and then he sees Olive going to the movies with Brutus.

episodes.name: The Medicine Man
episodes.overview: Olive begs Dr. Quack, aka Brutus, to cure Popeye's hiccups. But Dr. Quack wants Popeye's Spinach Health Juice off the market and Olive in his clutches.

episodes.name: A Mite of Trouble
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag tries to steal Popeyes treasure map treasure map by dressing a dwarf up as Swee'pea.

episodes.name: Who's Kidding Zoo
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus apply for the same part-time zoo keeper job.

episodes.name: Robot Popeye
episodes.overview: Brutus buys a Popeye robot to cause friction between Popeye and Olive.

episodes.name: Sneaking Peeking
episodes.overview: Christmas Eve is here, with Popeye and Olive Oyl trying to stop Swee'pea from peeking into the Christmas presents. Popeye tells him a fable; something like Pandora's Box. Will Swee'pea learn?

episodes.name: Seer-ring Is Believer-ring
episodes.overview: Olive Oyl buys a ring that allows her to see the immediate future; but it really belongs to Evil Eye, a red-bearded foreign hypnotist with supernatural powers.

episodes.name: The Wiffle Bird's Revenge
episodes.overview: The Wiffle bird casts a spell over Wimpy that changes him into a werewolf whenever he says the word "hamburger".

episodes.name: Going Going Gone
episodes.overview: Wimpy tricks Brutus into buying him some hamburgers, Brutus gets angry and Wimpy decides to use vanishing cream to hide from him.

episodes.name: Popeye Thumb
episodes.overview: Popeye tells Swee' Pea the story of "Popeye Thumb".

episodes.name: The Billionaire
episodes.overview: Billionaire Popeye gives a million dollars to each of his friends to see who will spend the money the wisest way. When they squander all their money and ask for more, Popeye decides to give all the rest of his money to the Poor Sailor Fund.

episodes.name: Model Muddle
episodes.overview: After visiting the national art museum Popeye decides to try his hand at a bit of modern sculpture.

episodes.name: Which Is Witch
episodes.overview: The Sea Hag hatches a plot to kidnap Popeye. She replaces Olive with a robot replica programmed to bring him to her Island.

episodes.name: Disguise the Limit
episodes.overview: Popeye the Detective is called on to find a gorilla that has just escaped from the Zoo. He an Olive devise a plan to re-capture the gorilla which involves Popeye disguising himself as a female gorilla and luring it back into it enclosure.

episodes.name: Spoil Sport
episodes.overview: Popeye has got himself a scooter, Olive Snubs him for Brutus and his fast, shiny, new, fast sports car. The ride turns out to be far too fast and dangerous for Olive and it's not long before she is in need of help from Popeye.

episodes.name: Have Time Will Travel
episodes.overview: Popeye, who is presumably bored of living in the 1960, decides to build Olive a time machine, luckily the dinosaur populated prehistoric time they visit has plenty of spinach.

episodes.name: Weight for Me
episodes.overview: Popeye and Brutus return from six months at sea to find that Olive has gotten fat. Brutus indulges Olive's lust for food, while Popeye tries to force her to exercise.

episodes.name: Partial Post
episodes.overview: Popeye accidentally posts Olive Oyl's birthdays cards into a recently landed spaceship, thinking it to be a mailbox.

episodes.name: Canine Caprice
episodes.overview: Popeye buys Olive Oyl a talking dog, the dog, named Roger, tells Popeye that Olive Oyl has been seeing another man.

episodes.name: Intellectual Interlude
episodes.overview: Popeye eats some "intellectual spinach" given to him by a professor at an adult education class.

episodes.name: Roger
episodes.overview: Roger, the talking dog, discovers a plot to rob a jewelry store but he is unable to get the police to understand him.

episodes.name: Tooth Be or Not Tooth Be
episodes.overview: Swee' Pea is cutting a tooth, PoopDeck Pappy decides to give Swee' Pea a lesson in dental hygiene and tells him a story of what happened to him when he entered a "teeth" contest.
